WEBVTT

00:10:29.901 --> 00:10:31.074
It's astonishing.

00:10:31.098 --> 00:10:32.771
And putting that data together --

00:10:32.795 --> 00:10:35.290
you can see the looting pits marked here.

00:10:36.442 --> 00:10:41.733
At one site, the looting got bad
from 2009, 2011, 2012 --

00:10:41.757 --> 00:10:43.318
hundreds and hundreds of pits.

00:10:43.784 --> 00:10:45.215
Putting all the data together,

00:10:45.239 --> 00:10:48.290
what we found is that,
contrary to popular opinion,

00:10:48.314 --> 00:10:53.375
looting did not start to get worse
in Egypt in 2011 after the Arab Spring,

00:10:53.399 --> 00:10:56.991
but in 2009, after the global recession.

00:10:57.531 --> 00:11:00.160
Thus, we've shown with big data